## Run locally
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
# open http://localhost:3000  (uses a local SQLite file, no database needed)
```

If Railway ever doesn't auto-pick the start command, set it manually:
service → Settings → Deploy → Custom Start Command → `python app.py`

## How the two key requirements work
- **Answers update for everyone:** published answers are written to the database
  and served from it; the front page re-fetches every 30 seconds so all visitors
  stay in sync.
- **Only Lurlene gets popups:** popups come from `/api/admin/new-since`, which is
  behind the admin login. Only her logged-in browser polls it, so only she sees
  the breaking-news alerts.

## For real-world use
Change `ADMIN_PASS`, set a strong `SESSION_SECRET`, and consider hashing the
password (e.g. with `werkzeug.security`) instead of the plain comparison used
here for simplicity.
